20/09/2009
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- French General Arnaud Sainte-Claire Deville took over command Thursday (September 17th) of KFOR Sector North where a French contingent is deployed.
He replaced General Patrick Ribayrol.
A total of 2,300 troops from France, Morocco, Belgium, Denmark, Estonia, Greece and Luxembourg are serving in KFOR Sector North.
Their main task is to prevent ethnic conflicts in the region, maintain security at the border with Serbia and monitor the situation in the ethnically divided town of Mitrovica.
(AFP, Adevarul, French Defence Ministry website - 18/09/09)
